# Combining Protocols

Structs cannot inherit from other Structs.
But **Protocols CAN inherit from other Protocols!**

```swift
protocol Payable {
    func calculateWage() -> Int
}

// Employee inherits the Payable rules, AND adds its own!
protocol Employee: Payable {
    var jobTitle: String { get }
}
```
If a Struct adopts the `Employee` protocol, it is now strictly forced to provide BOTH `jobTitle` AND `calculateWage()`!

# Signing Many Contracts

Unlike Class inheritance (where a child can only ever have ONE single parent), a Struct or Class can adopt as many Protocols as it wants at the exact same time!

You separate each Protocol with a comma `,`.

```swift
// The User class inherits from Person AND adopts 2 protocols
class User: Person, Comparable, Equatable {
    // Code that fulfills all rules goes here
}
```
